company_commercial_names: chiba urban monorail | chiba urban monorail 千葉都市モノレール | monorail urbain de chiba
short_description: chiba urban monorail is a railroad service company based in chiba, japan.
long_description: the chiba urban monorail (千葉都市モノレール) is a two-line suspended monorail system located in chiba, chiba prefecture, japan. it is owned and operated by chiba urban monorail co., ltd (千葉都市モノレール株式会社), a so-called "third-sector" company established on march 20, 1979. investors include the city of chiba. the first segment (line 2 from sports center station to chishirodai station) opened on march 28, 1988, also the rest by march 24, 1999. the pasmo contactless smart card can be used to purchase fares.
generated_description: chiba urban monorail, also known as chiba urban monorail co., ltd (千葉都市モノレール株式会社), is a japanese company that operates a two-line suspended monorailing system in chiba, chiba prefecture. established in 1979, it is owned and operated by chiba city monorailing co., limited, a third-sector company. the company's first segment, line 2 from sports center station to chishirodai station, opened on march 28, 1988, with the rest of the line opening on march 24, 1999. the pasmo contactless smart card can be used to purchase fares.
